cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.GR 

The paper focuses on visualizing convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and proposes a visual grammar for this purpose. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the analysis of figures from ICCV and CVPR papers, which suggests that it could belong to cs.GR (Graphics) as well. Finally, the paper involves the automation of network visualization, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
